WEBVTT

00:24.640 --> 00:27.130
Good morning, Marielle.

00:27.180 --> 00:28.780
This is our home for the summer.

00:30.430 --> 00:31.840
I grew up in this place.

00:31.890 --> 00:32.890
It's beautiful here.

00:38.660 --> 00:40.270
Let's start clearing Nana's

00:40.320 --> 00:41.990
boxes to make space for the family.

00:43.630 --> 00:46.590
Tomorrow you will meet everyone.

03:48.690 --> 03:50.210
- You're awake too?

03:50.260 --> 03:53.670
A little.

04:00.060 --> 04:01.490
Hey, Marielle?
- Hm?

04:01.540 --> 04:02.820
- Happy birthday.

04:04.040 --> 04:07.450
Thank you, nounette.

04:23.570 --> 04:24.350
- Marielle's up.

04:24.400 --> 04:25.670
Why don't you go say hello?

04:30.370 --> 04:31.470
This is nice.

04:39.730 --> 04:40.560
- Hello there.

04:46.630 --> 04:51.020
- So, you're going to cook for us tonight?

04:51.070 --> 04:53.510
We finally get to see it for ourselves.

04:54.360 --> 04:56.470
- Don't make such a big deal of it.

04:56.520 --> 05:00.340
- This is our first family
meal together in years.

05:01.290 --> 05:04.070
I'm sorry if this is not
particularly important to you.

05:04.120 --> 05:06.030
- I mean, there's been
plenty of times when-

05:06.080 --> 05:09.000
- Roland, what is Marielle allergic to?

05:11.650 --> 05:13.050
Exactly.

05:13.100 --> 05:15.450
It's our first time all together

05:15.500 --> 05:17.420
since I took her to France with me.

05:19.720 --> 05:24.200
Marielle never had a
father figure in her life.

05:24.250 --> 05:26.830
She needs to spend some time with you.

05:33.700 --> 05:36.380
It's so nice to see you
sisters together again.

05:36.430 --> 05:38.560
Ada is growing so fast.

05:46.020 --> 05:48.080
I am not getting involved, but

05:49.530 --> 05:51.230
if you're ready to start,

05:51.280 --> 05:53.150
I could find you a contractor.

05:53.200 --> 05:53.980
- Really? You don't

05:54.030 --> 05:55.620
want to sign off on this first?

05:55.670 --> 05:56.500
- No, darling.

05:57.380 --> 05:59.420
I just want you to be in good hands.

06:03.550 --> 06:06.240
- So, what are you gonna try first?

06:06.290 --> 06:10.700
My bean cassoulet or my risotto?

06:10.750 --> 06:12.090
I don't mind.

06:12.140 --> 06:13.140
- Whatever you want.

06:27.270 --> 06:28.650
- Okay, I'm ready.

06:32.410 --> 06:33.240
Roland?

06:50.440 --> 06:51.270
Hello?

06:52.370 --> 06:54.290
Oh, hi, Hugo.

06:55.350 --> 06:56.670
Good.

06:56.720 --> 06:58.090
Do you want to speak to her?

07:01.230 --> 07:03.780
Guess who's looking for you?

07:03.830 --> 07:04.610
- Who?

07:04.660 --> 07:05.850
- Say hello.

07:05.900 --> 07:06.730
- Hello.

07:09.030 --> 07:10.220
Hi, daddy.

07:16.830 --> 07:18.510
- Thanks for waiting for me.

07:20.290 --> 07:23.040
- Ask me before giving the phone to her.

07:23.090 --> 07:25.240
- Her father wanted to speak with her.

07:25.290 --> 07:26.260
- When our dad wanted

07:26.310 --> 07:28.490
to do that sometimes you wouldn't let him.

07:28.540 --> 07:30.810
- It's not the same thing.

07:30.860 --> 07:31.690
- It is.

07:33.820 --> 07:34.720
I have my reasons.

07:43.070 --> 07:44.870
- You have both become so beautiful.

07:48.210 --> 07:49.630
I regret missing the years,

07:52.600 --> 07:54.600
but I intend to make that up to you now,

07:56.290 --> 07:57.400
to be with my girls.

08:01.680 --> 08:04.330
Marielle, welcome to England.

08:05.210 --> 08:06.040
Welcome home.

08:08.560 --> 08:11.290
Adrienne, you'e gonna
renovate your childhood home.

08:11.340 --> 08:13.660
I mean, what a gift that is.

08:15.350 --> 08:17.720
- This was my childhood home, Roland.

08:17.770 --> 08:18.820
This was my mother's

08:18.870 --> 08:20.360
house, let's not forget that.

08:20.410 --> 08:24.250
- Oh, annoying, nagging Nadine who I love.

08:24.300 --> 08:28.540
- Roland, just pass me the salad please.

08:33.670 --> 08:38.670
- So lucky we are to
spend the summer together.

08:41.800 --> 08:45.300
The
besest way to start my retiraaament!

08:48.390 --> 08:51.130
And to start it with
Marielle's 16th birthday

08:51.180 --> 08:52.430
is even more special.

08:55.290 --> 08:57.470
My little laves...

08:57.520 --> 09:00.280
the house is welcoming us to reconnect!

09:02.040 --> 09:05.710
I'm tired.

09:07.180 --> 09:08.990
She's 18.

09:10.060 --> 09:11.910
How do you think that makes her feel?

09:32.080 --> 09:35.800
Ada, let me help you.

09:35.850 --> 09:37.600
- For you.
- For me?

09:38.800 --> 09:40.460
- For your birthday.

09:41.680 --> 09:45.100
Thank you, nounette.

09:51.900 --> 09:54.460
- Thank you for your speech tonight.

09:54.510 --> 09:55.500
I'm proud of you.

09:55.550 --> 09:57.010
- Wait, let me finish my page.

10:06.290 --> 10:08.580
- Sorry to have interrupted your reading.

10:14.360 --> 10:18.840
It took my mother dying
for you to come back?

10:18.890 --> 10:20.460
- You left me, Nadine.

10:20.510 --> 10:21.440
You drove away.

10:21.490 --> 10:23.020
What for? To bring up our

10:23.070 --> 10:24.440
daughter on your own? Away

10:24.490 --> 10:26.570
from her father, away from her sister?

10:29.630 --> 10:31.000
- I drove away,

10:34.610 --> 10:36.760
but you could still have been their dad.

10:44.870 --> 10:45.650
- I'm sorry.

10:45.700 --> 10:48.450
I know how tough things have been for you.

10:51.810 --> 10:52.640
- Look,

10:57.750 --> 10:59.500
we were both unhappy.

11:00.740 --> 11:02.220
I wasn't naive anymore.

11:05.230 --> 11:06.450
- But that doesn't matter.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.330
We are here now.

11:09.530 --> 11:10.310
Are you upset

11:10.360 --> 11:12.180
because I try to get closer to her?

11:13.620 --> 11:15.020
- No.

11:15.070 --> 11:15.850
- Then what is it?

11:15.900 --> 11:17.070
You miss the theater?

11:20.260 --> 11:21.680
- A bit.

11:21.730 --> 11:22.560
- Ah.

11:24.560 --> 11:26.660
You don't think I find you sexy anymore.

11:26.710 --> 11:27.760
- Stop it.

11:28.600 --> 11:30.060
Those new panties eh?

11:30.110 --> 11:31.280
- Stop talking.

11:33.030 --> 11:36.730
I just want us to be better
parents this time around.

11:38.870 --> 11:41.640
And for you to know how
old your daughter is.

11:42.750 --> 11:45.050
Well, she
just seems a lot younger.

13:07.800 --> 13:11.210
Son of a bitch!

13:29.930 --> 13:31.550
- You know what?

13:31.600 --> 13:33.510
I changed my mind flowers.

13:33.560 --> 13:35.440
Flowers are important.

13:36.750 --> 13:40.020
My mother filled this
house with all sorts of...

13:40.070 --> 13:42.200
- We already agreed on the decking area.

13:42.250 --> 13:44.040
We can't keep doing this.

13:44.090 --> 13:47.560
I won't be able to work with
you if every five minutes...

13:47.610 --> 13:49.520
- Adrienne, listen to me.

13:49.570 --> 13:52.600
This BnB was her dream.

13:52.650 --> 13:54.210
I need to honor that now.

13:55.860 --> 13:57.420
She loved her flowers.

13:58.640 --> 14:00.270
Don't you remember?

14:00.320 --> 14:01.170
- I do, yes.

14:01.220 --> 14:02.640
I also remember how you used

14:02.690 --> 14:04.510
to scream at Nana Lottie sometimes,

14:04.560 --> 14:06.450
not getting rid of anything,

14:06.500 --> 14:09.840
piling up too much stuff,
for living in the past.

14:11.230 --> 14:13.580
Don't be like her, maman.

14:13.630 --> 14:14.460
- Fine.

14:15.400 --> 14:17.100
But that's not true.

14:17.150 --> 14:19.380
I never raised my voice.

14:19.430 --> 14:21.480
You must've just interpreted it that way.

14:22.440 --> 14:24.160
- You have to trust me, all right?

14:25.670 --> 14:26.820
I'm doing this for you.

14:29.600 --> 14:31.820
- Ah, it's Ada.

14:31.870 --> 14:32.700
Ada.

14:35.220 --> 14:36.000
Yes.

14:36.050 --> 14:37.500
What do you want to do?

14:38.660 --> 14:40.000
- Find Marielle.

15:16.220 --> 15:17.610
Did you find her?

15:17.660 --> 15:18.830
Do you want an ice pop?

15:21.350 --> 15:23.680
Why don't you give it to Ada?

15:23.730 --> 15:24.690
- I can't.

15:25.930 --> 15:27.030
I'm working right now.

15:28.130 --> 15:30.180
- Adrienne, I'm not her mother.

15:36.570 --> 15:37.350
- No one seems to

15:37.400 --> 15:39.060
know what it is to work anymore.

15:40.370 --> 15:42.070
- Don't be like this.

15:42.120 --> 15:44.520
- We're all here to be
together, all right?

15:46.490 --> 15:49.750
Where is Marielle?

15:49.800 --> 15:51.760
- You didn't find her?

15:51.810 --> 15:52.640
Where is she?

15:53.820 --> 15:55.230
Roland, come with me.

15:55.280 --> 15:56.250
We have to go now.

16:28.710 --> 16:32.060
Everyone when they're too
young wants to run away.

16:35.800 --> 16:36.680
- Should I drive?

16:36.730 --> 16:37.560
I'm sorry.

16:40.000 --> 16:40.930
- Let me go alone.

16:42.730 --> 16:44.210
She's not used to you yet.

16:45.780 --> 16:49.220
I thought all of us coming here together

16:49.270 --> 16:54.270
would make her warm to this
place, but I'm worried, Roland.

16:54.320 --> 16:55.150
I'm worried.

16:59.040 --> 17:00.090
Where did I go wrong?

17:00.960 --> 17:02.180
- Crustaceans!

17:02.230 --> 17:03.550
- What?

17:03.600 --> 17:05.670
- Well, that's what
she's allergic to, right?

17:06.840 --> 17:11.250
- Roland, I have a feeling
she ventured to the water.

17:17.350 --> 17:19.660
- You always have a good feelings.

17:42.230 --> 17:45.150
Marielle!

17:45.200 --> 17:50.200
Marielle!

17:53.100 --> 17:54.270
My little girl!

17:54.320 --> 17:55.580
What's happened?

17:55.630 --> 17:59.050
I wanted
to swim, but then I got lost and-

18:00.010 --> 18:01.000
- Well of course you

18:01.050 --> 18:02.900
got lost. You don't remember this place.

18:04.340 --> 18:07.730
Be careful!

18:07.780 --> 18:10.670
- Here, keep it.

18:12.220 --> 18:13.900
Thank you.

18:13.950 --> 18:16.680
Thank you for rescuing her.

18:17.620 --> 18:18.450
- No trouble.

18:23.410 --> 18:25.400
- Well, it was nice to meet you.

18:25.450 --> 18:26.280
Thank you.

18:27.200 --> 18:28.490
We should go now,

18:28.540 --> 18:31.160
otherwise my husband will
think I've abandoned him.

18:31.210 --> 18:32.620
- Have you?

18:32.670 --> 18:33.510
- What?

18:34.750 --> 18:36.780
- Abandoned him, so to speak.

18:36.830 --> 18:39.390
I don't know
why my relationship

18:39.440 --> 18:41.420
should interest a stranger.

18:41.470 --> 18:45.760
- You almost ran into
me earlier on the road.

18:47.310 --> 18:48.580
- Earlier on the road?

18:48.630 --> 18:49.460
- See?

18:51.510 --> 18:52.960
I wouldn't call us strangers.

18:54.130 --> 18:55.570
- She's only just 18.

18:56.990 --> 18:58.410
We're going home.

19:06.300 --> 19:08.440
- He didn't mean it, you know.

19:08.490 --> 19:09.610
Your dad.

19:09.660 --> 19:13.960
You were so excited to
come here as a child.

19:14.010 --> 19:16.010
Nana Lottie loved you very much.

19:18.370 --> 19:23.370
Please, Marielle, I need
you to give this a chance.

19:23.420 --> 19:25.220
You can't just leave me like this.

19:25.270 --> 19:26.290
You can't.

19:26.340 --> 19:29.760
I'm not used to it.
I can't sleep with her boxes piled in my room.

19:31.950 --> 19:34.360
I'm not mad
at papa, but it's weird.

19:34.410 --> 19:35.870
We're kind of like strangers.

19:35.920 --> 19:37.980
- He reads a lot, like you.

19:39.490 --> 19:41.530
You have more in common than you think.

19:44.120 --> 19:45.630
I took a wrong turn.

19:45.680 --> 19:47.670
I don't recognize this road.

19:47.720 --> 19:51.810
It's easy to get lost here.

19:51.860 --> 19:53.760
Just be careful, all right?

19:55.110 --> 19:58.160
I never really knew my father
because of the car accident.

19:59.260 --> 20:01.100
Your head is always in the clouds...

20:01.150 --> 20:03.970
Mum I know.

20:04.020 --> 20:05.570
Do you like him?

20:05.620 --> 20:08.190
Well yeah, he's my dad...

20:08.240 --> 20:10.010
- That's not who I meant.

20:10.060 --> 20:12.090
It's okay, Marielle.

20:12.140 --> 20:14.220
You're allowed to want to like somebody.

20:16.610 --> 20:17.440
- Vases.

20:19.160 --> 20:20.710
- Ah, perfect.

20:22.380 --> 20:23.210
Okay.

20:27.890 --> 20:29.010
This one, this one.

20:29.060 --> 20:30.980
Yeah, perfect.

20:31.030 --> 20:34.550
- But we're packing up
these boxes for the BnB, no?

20:34.600 --> 20:35.850
Why are you opening them?

20:37.010 --> 20:38.180
- Because they're

20:38.230 --> 20:40.160
beautiful pieces. We could use these, mum.

20:40.210 --> 20:42.260
- Don't you think Nana
Lottie would like it?

20:42.310 --> 20:44.510
- It's just, it's not ready. We haven't

20:44.560 --> 20:46.450
even started the building work.

20:46.500 --> 20:47.810
- Smile!

20:47.860 --> 20:50.080
- Put that away, Roland.

20:50.130 --> 20:52.440
You can't just do whatever you want.

20:52.490 --> 20:54.370
Mum it's no big deal.

20:54.420 --> 20:55.800
- Just leave it, okay?

20:55.850 --> 20:57.260
And plus it was daddy who-

20:57.310 --> 20:59.790
- Oh, of course it was daddy.

21:12.830 --> 21:14.140
This is what my

21:14.190 --> 21:15.770
mum and sister look like

21:15.820 --> 21:17.130
together. It's strange to

21:17.180 --> 21:18.840
think that mum had a whole other

21:19.690 --> 21:21.160
life before me, raising

21:22.030 --> 21:23.680
Adrienne with dad. Is this what

21:23.730 --> 21:24.890
they would do?

21:24.940 --> 21:26.880
Play house? Make arts and crafts?

21:26.930 --> 21:29.700
Before Adrienne left and
mum and dad were fighting,

21:29.750 --> 21:30.880
before I was born,

21:32.030 --> 21:34.200
sometimes I imagine Adrienne's childhood

21:34.250 --> 21:35.500
as if it were my own.

21:44.780 --> 21:48.190
“I drift toward waves”
“With fog in my eyes
A boat arises”

21:54.170 --> 21:54.950
Sorry, Nick,

21:55.000 --> 21:56.550
but this won't work out anymore.

21:56.600 --> 21:58.520
Thank you so much for your help so far.

21:58.570 --> 22:00.450
- After everything I've done for you?

22:00.500 --> 22:03.630
I came here and I saved this place.

22:03.680 --> 22:05.330
I made it beautiful.

22:07.830 --> 22:09.680
Lucy, I don't know where else to go.

22:12.700 --> 22:13.530
Please.

22:14.620 --> 22:15.930
- I'm sorry.

22:15.980 --> 22:18.160
Nick, don't take it badly.

22:19.800 --> 22:20.580
We can be friends.

22:20.630 --> 22:21.460
- Don't touch me.

22:22.750 --> 22:25.900
Don't look at me like
I'm some sad, worthless

22:25.950 --> 22:27.180
"son of a bitch"!

22:27.230 --> 22:28.010
You know what?

22:28.060 --> 22:29.530
I'm the one who feels bad for you,

22:29.580 --> 22:31.350
to be stuck in a place like this.

22:31.400 --> 22:32.770
Where you goin' with your life?

22:32.820 --> 22:34.390
It's a dead end road here.

22:35.360 --> 22:36.610
A fucking dead end road!

22:58.660 --> 22:59.490
You ok?

23:05.490 --> 23:07.640
- No one ever really cares, kid.

23:11.740 --> 23:13.970
You try and make an effort,

23:16.900 --> 23:19.300
and then everything disappears.

23:24.410 --> 23:25.240
Fuck!

23:28.070 --> 23:28.900
- Hey.

23:34.040 --> 23:34.880
It's okay.

23:44.270 --> 23:46.630
So... "son on a bitch"...

23:46.680 --> 23:48.290
Remember that phrase?

23:48.340 --> 23:49.190
- What can I say?

23:50.060 --> 23:51.060
It stuck in my head.

23:59.230 --> 24:00.990
- We're changing our house.

24:01.040 --> 24:02.570
You want to help?

24:02.620 --> 24:03.930
- Oh, no, no, no.

24:03.980 --> 24:05.750
Got some plans...

24:05.800 --> 24:07.300
- You may like it.

24:13.660 --> 24:15.410
- Your English isn't bad, you know.

24:27.750 --> 24:29.050
- Where should I put this?

24:31.480 --> 24:33.980
- Up there I suppose.

24:34.030 --> 24:35.530
- Over the mirror?

24:40.410 --> 24:42.140
- What is that?

24:42.190 --> 24:44.200
- I had it made.

24:44.250 --> 24:46.000
You know what?

24:46.050 --> 24:47.030
Nevermind.

24:48.180 --> 24:50.170
God forbid you should become a little

24:50.220 --> 24:51.350
romantic once in a while.

24:51.400 --> 24:52.180
- All right...

24:52.230 --> 24:54.240
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

24:56.700 --> 24:58.440
Come on, come give me a cuddle.

24:58.490 --> 24:59.320
Come on.

25:06.580 --> 25:10.330
- I decided to try it
again once and for all.

25:13.820 --> 25:16.200
There's plenty of roles for older women,

25:16.250 --> 25:17.070
and I'm sure I...

25:17.120 --> 25:18.410
and I'll play for Arsenal.

25:18.460 --> 25:19.460
How does that sound?

25:20.470 --> 25:21.740
- I'm serious.

25:21.790 --> 25:23.300
- Yeah, pull the other one.

25:28.510 --> 25:31.460
This is the
last audition I'll try.

25:31.510 --> 25:34.020
Please don't ruin it for me.

25:34.070 --> 25:35.430
- Don't be like that.

25:50.250 --> 25:52.210
- Marielle, no.

25:52.260 --> 25:54.850
We've had enough of the
swimming, all right?

25:54.900 --> 25:56.640
Come, run some errands with me.

25:59.840 --> 26:03.320
Marielle, I'm sorry, but I'm your mother

26:03.370 --> 26:05.710
and that shirt is really disgusting.

26:05.760 --> 26:07.180
Whatever.

26:07.230 --> 26:09.040
It looks really ugly on you.

26:09.090 --> 26:10.690
It's as if you do it on purpose.

26:16.030 --> 26:20.750
- I am just listening to
this sexy '80s superstar.

26:23.350 --> 26:25.360
- Stop it, Roland!

26:35.750 --> 26:37.130
- Mummy?

26:37.180 --> 26:38.960
I want to go on a bike ride.

26:39.010 --> 26:40.340
I'm bored.

26:41.310 --> 26:43.180
Not right now.

26:43.230 --> 26:44.660
But daddy says...

26:44.710 --> 26:46.480
- Look, your bike is broken.

26:46.530 --> 26:48.030
When I've got time, I'll fix it

26:48.080 --> 26:49.280
and then we'll go, okay?

26:52.010 --> 26:55.160
Okay.

26:55.210 --> 26:57.450
Where is this song from?

26:57.500 --> 26:59.280
- When I first met your father,

27:00.150 --> 27:01.910
he helped me to make an album.

27:03.180 --> 27:06.600
Oh right,
that's really nice. Do you miss it?

27:10.010 --> 27:11.000
Sometimes.

27:12.650 --> 27:16.670
But the spotlight was a
mere moment in a lifetime

27:16.720 --> 27:20.680
of standing right next to it, in the dark.

27:28.050 --> 27:28.880
- Ada?

27:34.180 --> 27:36.260
Are you in here, sweetie?

27:37.290 --> 27:39.290
Where'd she go?

27:39.340 --> 27:40.170
Ada?

27:46.200 --> 27:48.250
Ada!

27:48.300 --> 27:53.230
Where are you?

27:53.280 --> 27:54.110
Ada?

27:55.070 --> 27:57.750
It's not funny anymore.

27:57.800 --> 27:59.150
Ada, where are you sweetie?

28:14.590 --> 28:15.590
- Hello little girl.

28:16.430 --> 28:17.380
Is your mummy home?

28:23.460 --> 28:24.290
Come.

28:39.690 --> 28:42.240
- Who are you and what are
you doing with my child?

28:44.800 --> 28:48.130
- I hear you're in need of some fixing up.

28:55.970 --> 28:58.330
- Thanks for bringing her back.

28:58.380 --> 28:59.320
Did anyone

28:59.370 --> 29:01.460
tell you how strikingly beautiful you are?

29:17.390 --> 29:18.890
- You look beautiful, darling.

29:21.560 --> 29:22.390
Stop fidgeting.

29:33.480 --> 29:36.730
