31:53.100 --> 31:55.560
Do you want me to call daddy?

31:57.470 --> 31:59.040
Do you want daddy to come visit?

31:59.090 --> 31:59.920
- Yes.

32:02.020 --> 32:02.890
I'm not

32:02.940 --> 32:05.760
swimming much because it
worries mum, since that time.

32:05.810 --> 32:08.290
In Paris, mum's flat is
on such a noisy street

32:08.340 --> 32:10.240
I can never hear myself think.

32:10.290 --> 32:11.950
That's why I like him.

32:12.000 --> 32:14.690
He's quiet, but he says a lot.

32:15.590 --> 32:16.810
A peaceful landscape.

32:18.890 --> 32:20.660
- I love your vision and passion.

32:22.660 --> 32:24.450
The lake house is gonna be perfect.

32:24.500 --> 32:28.300
You're brimming with excitement
right now, it's cute.

32:28.350 --> 32:29.960
- Turn the page.

32:31.190 --> 32:32.020
What's next?

32:34.450 --> 32:35.320
- Leave it with me.

32:35.370 --> 32:36.420
I'll survey the area.

32:38.630 --> 32:42.050
Mummy will tell you.

32:44.600 --> 32:45.430
Ada?

32:59.600 --> 33:00.430
- Nice view.

33:04.730 --> 33:05.910
- Fuck.

33:08.310 --> 33:09.920
- Can I see the photo?

33:09.970 --> 33:11.480
- Hi.

33:11.530 --> 33:12.360
Yeah, Em.

33:13.320 --> 33:14.450
Hang on a minute.

33:48.010 --> 33:50.300
- Are you out of your mind?

33:50.350 --> 33:51.180
It's really hot.

33:52.740 --> 33:54.410
You need to get out of the sun.

33:54.460 --> 33:56.030
It's fine.

33:56.080 --> 33:56.920
It's not.

33:57.820 --> 33:58.650
It's not fine.

34:04.720 --> 34:07.350
Daddy's also reading this.

34:07.400 --> 34:09.060
Oh really?

34:09.110 --> 34:10.310
You two are buddies now?

34:11.290 --> 34:14.710
I know what I'm doing.

34:18.390 --> 34:19.220
You're 18.

34:31.920 --> 34:32.830
- Where are you going?

34:32.880 --> 34:34.280
We're going cycling!

34:35.800 --> 34:38.490
- But look, it's clouding over.

34:40.310 --> 34:42.070
I'm taking our crustacean

34:42.120 --> 34:43.820
daughter out for lunch!

34:43.870 --> 34:46.170
- But it looks like rain.

34:47.380 --> 34:48.550
- Come on.

34:48.600 --> 34:49.880
Yes!

34:49.930 --> 34:50.760
Woo!

34:52.580 --> 34:53.420
Go.

34:56.270 --> 34:57.050
- Papa?

34:57.100 --> 34:57.930
- Yes, darling?

34:57.980 --> 34:59.420
Try it in English.

35:05.550 --> 35:07.460
- Ok. What do you
think if I took a year off

35:07.510 --> 35:10.160
before starting university in Lille?

35:12.200 --> 35:14.010
- Why would you want to do that?

35:14.060 --> 35:15.240
I dunno...

35:15.290 --> 35:18.190
- I just don't want to go back to France.

35:19.300 --> 35:21.430
If I were to try something adventurous,

35:21.480 --> 35:23.060
shouldn't it be now?

35:23.110 --> 35:24.630
- Like what?

35:24.680 --> 35:27.440
- Like go with Adrienne maybe.

35:28.360 --> 35:30.080
I know she has her building project,

35:30.130 --> 35:34.780
but I could work just
to get some experience.

35:34.830 --> 35:36.180
- Thanks, Paul.

35:36.230 --> 35:39.130
I think that is a most excellent idea.

35:39.180 --> 35:40.980
You remind me of me back in the day.

35:57.240 --> 35:58.590
- "Whoever you are,

35:58.640 --> 36:01.970
I have always depended on
the kindness of strangers."

36:03.220 --> 36:04.720
- What?

36:04.770 --> 36:05.600
- Nothing.

36:07.540 --> 36:08.630
Thank you for coming.

36:10.060 --> 36:12.470
Your dedication means a lot.

36:12.520 --> 36:13.470
- It's no big deal.

36:15.050 --> 36:17.560
Getting my hands dirty is the best part.

36:17.610 --> 36:18.860
Adrienne mentioned you'll

36:18.910 --> 36:20.260
be working on the deck now.

36:21.660 --> 36:22.710
- That's right, boss.

36:34.210 --> 36:35.480
- What's the matter?

36:35.530 --> 36:37.100
- I'm too hot and too tired.

36:40.530 --> 36:41.320
- Okay.

36:41.370 --> 36:44.270
Well, should we go and
get you some ice pops?

36:44.320 --> 36:45.760
Yes?

36:45.810 --> 36:47.880
And when you come visit me, we

36:47.930 --> 36:49.470
could get you some then too, I'll

36:49.520 --> 36:50.430
Ihave lots of them.

36:50.480 --> 36:52.460
Lots of lots for you, yes?

36:52.510 --> 36:53.970
Would you like that?

36:54.020 --> 36:55.450
Yeah?

36:55.500 --> 36:56.280
Okay.

36:56.330 --> 36:57.330
You know what?

36:58.630 --> 37:00.550
We need to be tough, buddy.

37:01.400 --> 37:02.800
Say, "I am tough."

37:02.850 --> 37:03.750
- I am tough.

37:03.800 --> 37:05.410
- Yes.

37:05.460 --> 37:06.290
Come.

37:08.810 --> 37:11.010
- And that's how you
make an old fashioned.

37:14.150 --> 37:17.170
This is how a true lady impresses a man.

37:17.220 --> 37:18.000
- Papa...

37:18.050 --> 37:22.010
- But, the most important
thing is the orange peel.

37:23.480 --> 37:24.310
Of course.

37:28.340 --> 37:29.170
- You're lucky.

37:55.380 --> 37:58.420
- Yes please, some water.

37:58.470 --> 37:59.550
Oh, thanks, sweetheart.

37:59.600 --> 38:02.130
That was great fun.

38:02.180 --> 38:03.590
Yes, I know, I know!

38:03.640 --> 38:06.480
I am running in the
house with muddy shoes!

38:06.530 --> 38:07.360
Ah!

38:10.270 --> 38:13.180
- Marielle, I've been doing
a lot of thinking today...

38:13.230 --> 38:15.650
Not now, mum.

38:15.700 --> 38:17.100
- Why do you look so weird?

38:18.790 --> 38:19.790
- I did my hair.

38:22.630 --> 38:23.950
- I'm going for a run.

38:24.000 --> 38:25.260
- But you'll get sick!

38:39.480 --> 38:40.320
- Hey.

38:44.400 --> 38:46.260
- Why did you ignore me yesterday?

39:01.020 --> 39:01.850
- Where?

39:03.190 --> 39:06.120
- Back by the bushes, after the pond.

39:16.960 --> 39:17.790
Nevermind.

39:23.150 --> 39:23.980
- Put this back.

39:39.510 --> 39:41.240
I cut down some trees back there.

39:43.080 --> 39:45.410
I still need to clear the surface up.

39:45.460 --> 39:49.060
It's amazing actually, the amount of nature

39:49.110 --> 39:51.470
that gets tossed up from building works.

40:17.710 --> 40:19.910
What do you like most about it here?

40:19.960 --> 40:22.120
- I like the days where I wake up early.

40:27.570 --> 40:30.990
Naturally.

40:32.060 --> 40:33.720
When there's only a little bit of

40:33.770 --> 40:36.290
light out and the home is asleep.

41:04.910 --> 41:05.820
- How was your run?

41:05.870 --> 41:07.640
- Short, but sweet.

41:09.560 --> 41:11.620
- Would you like some company next time?

41:39.260 --> 41:40.090
- Hey, mum?

41:42.210 --> 41:44.560
I'm going to take a year
off before university.

41:45.430 --> 41:46.260
- What?

41:47.190 --> 41:48.240
Is that right?

41:48.290 --> 41:49.170
- Oui.

41:49.220 --> 41:51.970
Daddy and I agreed that I
should try another experience...

41:52.020 --> 41:53.280
- No, no, no, no.

41:53.330 --> 41:54.730
You can't just withdraw.

41:54.780 --> 41:55.810
- I know.

41:55.860 --> 41:56.900
I'm not withdrawing.

41:56.950 --> 41:58.760
I'm taking time off.

41:58.810 --> 42:01.830
- You're acting spoiled and ungrateful.

42:03.610 --> 42:06.480
I don't like this new English
attitude you've adopted.

42:07.340 --> 42:10.110
Come on, mum.

42:10.160 --> 42:11.040
What's wrong with-

42:11.090 --> 42:12.350
- Nothing's wrong with me.

42:12.400 --> 42:14.150
Why does everyone ask that?

42:15.240 --> 42:18.630
It's just that life is
hard sometimes, Marielle,

42:19.690 --> 42:22.190
and you can't just abandon someplace

42:22.240 --> 42:24.780
because right now you don't
feel like going to school.

42:24.830 --> 42:26.290
You're smarter than that.

42:26.340 --> 42:28.610
- But you're blowing it out of proportion.

42:28.660 --> 42:29.740
- I'm not.

42:32.160 --> 42:34.640
How come you're so sure you won't like it?

42:34.690 --> 42:36.970
You should at least give it a try.

42:37.020 --> 42:40.140
You can’t decide for me.
And Adrienne is leaving-

42:40.190 --> 42:41.390
- To further her career.

42:42.570 --> 42:45.060
She's been working on that
PhD project for years now.

42:45.110 --> 42:47.020
Come on, Marielle.

42:49.150 --> 42:52.570
Fine.

42:54.520 --> 42:57.590
- Okay, so how about if I
stayed at the house this year?

42:57.640 --> 43:00.240
I could use a quiet room
to improve my English

43:00.290 --> 43:02.090
and self-reflect.

43:02.140 --> 43:03.380
- Self-reflect?

43:04.400 --> 43:05.230
At the house?

43:07.890 --> 43:08.760
No, Marielle.

43:09.650 --> 43:13.270
Being an adult is about
accepting your choices

43:13.320 --> 43:15.430
and being responsible.

43:16.690 --> 43:20.690
For instance, there's this
play I'd like to audition for

43:20.740 --> 43:22.910
in an ideal world.

43:22.960 --> 43:25.810
But I can't just go off and be an actress.

43:25.860 --> 43:26.680
It's absurd.

43:26.730 --> 43:27.770
- You should do the play!

43:27.820 --> 43:29.500
- You need to think this through.

43:29.550 --> 43:31.050
- You should do the play, mum.

43:32.020 --> 43:33.230
I think that's great.

43:34.230 --> 43:35.530
- You should go to school!

43:37.870 --> 43:40.030
- Mum always says to be more adventurous,

43:40.080 --> 43:41.680
live life to the fullest.

43:41.730 --> 43:44.550
Being in love makes everything sweeter.

43:44.600 --> 43:47.820
Why does she always have to
complicate things with dad?

43:47.870 --> 43:48.880
My first portrait.

43:59.990 --> 44:01.890
- I'm glad you're going to see Claire.

44:02.860 --> 44:05.320
Maybe she can help you to reconsider, huh?

44:05.370 --> 44:06.990
Referee!

44:07.040 --> 44:09.140
- And don't forget on Sunday...

44:09.190 --> 44:12.410
There's
the audition. Of course I'll be there.

44:12.460 --> 44:13.740
Shoot!

44:13.790 --> 44:14.980
Oh, you donkey!

45:18.580 --> 45:19.790
- Speak French?

45:19.840 --> 45:20.620
- No.
- No?

45:21.500 --> 45:22.990
So you don't speak Italian?

45:23.040 --> 45:23.820
- A little bit.

45:23.870 --> 45:24.870
- A little bit?
- Ciao.

45:24.920 --> 45:26.040
- Oh, ciao.

45:26.090 --> 45:27.360
Bella...

45:27.410 --> 45:29.090
Two words, that's wonderful.

45:33.280 --> 45:36.920
Certo.

45:36.970 --> 45:37.970
Almost three.

45:38.020 --> 45:38.800
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

45:38.850 --> 45:40.060
- What do you mean almost?

45:40.110 --> 45:41.160
That was three.

45:41.210 --> 45:42.360
That was a solid three.

45:43.910 --> 45:45.990
- Hey, there you are.

45:49.020 --> 45:50.420
I should have picked you up.

45:52.370 --> 45:53.970
- It's okay.

45:54.020 --> 45:57.960
- Anyway, the reservation
is under Ventura.

45:58.010 --> 45:58.840
- Right.

46:01.090 --> 46:02.070
Ventura.

46:02.120 --> 46:04.190
Oh, here you are.

46:04.240 --> 46:05.590
Thanks for coming back here.

46:05.640 --> 46:06.780
Great.

46:06.830 --> 46:09.660
- Nick, you know about
continental breakfast, yeah?

46:09.710 --> 46:10.750
Yeah.

46:10.800 --> 46:12.050
- And Emily.

46:12.100 --> 46:14.030
Emily, you have...

46:14.080 --> 46:17.990
- Emily couldn't make
it, but this is Marielle.

46:19.220 --> 46:20.050
- Great.

46:22.680 --> 46:24.650
Here are the keys to your suite.

46:24.700 --> 46:25.530
- Thanks, Soph.

46:26.650 --> 46:27.750
- You're welcome.

46:27.800 --> 46:30.020
Tonight's acoustic night at the garden.

46:30.070 --> 46:30.900
- Great.

46:47.280 --> 46:48.110
- Wow.

46:49.140 --> 46:50.440
This is nice.

46:50.490 --> 46:51.320
- You're nice.

46:52.250 --> 46:53.090
And sweet.

46:56.170 --> 46:57.000
And beautiful.

47:05.440 --> 47:07.190
- That was embarrassing over there.

47:09.920 --> 47:10.750
Why?

47:11.720 --> 47:12.550
- Why?

47:17.320 --> 47:19.620
Did you bring me here as a backup?

47:19.670 --> 47:24.000
- Marielle, look, Emily's in the past.

47:24.050 --> 47:25.880
Yes, she's someone I knew.

47:28.730 --> 47:30.030
Now you're someone I know.

47:32.410 --> 47:33.820
- Really?

47:33.870 --> 47:34.700
- Yeah, kid.

48:06.370 --> 48:07.880
- Wait.

48:07.930 --> 48:08.760
- What?

48:09.790 --> 48:12.630
- Is it okay if we don't have sex?

