52:22.360 --> 52:24.870
- We decided against using
wood for the decking area.

52:24.920 --> 52:26.590
I said I wanted glass.

52:27.460 --> 52:29.740
- Well, we had some leftover timber

52:29.790 --> 52:31.820
from the upstairs window frames,

52:31.870 --> 52:33.220
so I thought we'd use that.

52:34.460 --> 52:36.030
- I said I wanted glass.

52:37.680 --> 52:40.230
Marielle, come help me tape
up the lake house area.

52:48.240 --> 52:49.020
- I don't know know

52:49.070 --> 52:51.040
why Adrienne keeps to herself so much.

52:51.090 --> 52:51.870
I want to tell her,

52:51.920 --> 52:54.130
but I know she would disapprove.

52:54.180 --> 52:56.050
My subject acts like I'm not here.

52:59.100 --> 53:00.360
- Just chop the tomatoes.

53:00.410 --> 53:03.510
- I am chopping the tomatoes.

53:03.560 --> 53:05.730
- What is that noise?

53:05.780 --> 53:06.620
- It's Hugo.

53:06.670 --> 53:09.010
He arrived a little bit
earlier, he's with Ada.

53:09.060 --> 53:11.480
- What's he doing, strangling her?

53:11.530 --> 53:12.360
- Just playing.

53:14.380 --> 53:15.160
That's him now.

53:15.210 --> 53:16.800
You'll get to meet him finally.

53:17.920 --> 53:18.750
- Hi.

53:21.300 --> 53:22.390
- Took the wrong turn?

53:22.440 --> 53:25.130
- I thought I'd stop by
and get extra work in.

53:25.180 --> 53:26.010
For you.

53:27.420 --> 53:31.350
It's a great one about
how the space of a home

53:31.400 --> 53:34.270
reflects the mentality
of the people in it.

53:34.320 --> 53:35.150
- Yes.

53:36.580 --> 53:38.560
I studied him in uni.

53:38.610 --> 53:41.060
That's very sweet.

53:44.950 --> 53:46.020
Oh, hi, Hugo.

53:47.230 --> 53:48.660
This is Nick.

53:48.710 --> 53:50.290
- Nick, contractor.

53:58.980 --> 54:00.400
- 17, 18, 19, 20.

54:04.680 --> 54:06.290
Coming, ready or not!

54:07.720 --> 54:09.820
He's taking a break?

54:09.870 --> 54:11.250
- Hey, where's Ada?

54:11.300 --> 54:13.550
- I don't know where Ada is.

54:19.630 --> 54:21.590
- Good of you to swing by.

54:21.640 --> 54:22.470
Have a beer.

54:25.150 --> 54:26.300
- This is lovely salad.

54:28.350 --> 54:30.530
You must be spending a
lot of time together.

54:35.700 --> 54:37.810
The house, it looks beautiful.

54:37.860 --> 54:38.970
What are the plans?

54:40.030 --> 54:41.400
- Yeah, it's going to be great.

54:41.450 --> 54:43.700
- Well, I think you better ask your wife.

54:43.750 --> 54:45.330
- We're going to have a lovely patio

54:45.380 --> 54:47.480
area designed by my beautiful daughter.

54:47.530 --> 54:48.490
- What is he doing?

54:48.540 --> 54:49.660
Pushups?

54:49.710 --> 54:50.780
Pull-ups?

54:53.330 --> 54:54.180
- Pushups.

54:55.590 --> 54:57.090
- It helps define the muscles.

54:59.020 --> 54:59.850
- Unbelievable.

55:05.600 --> 55:06.430
- Hi.

55:08.490 --> 55:11.170
- I didn't know we were all having lunch.

55:24.010 --> 55:25.570
Want to go to the beach?

55:25.620 --> 55:27.210
Mum, you know the one?

55:27.260 --> 55:28.800
- Well, Ada doesn't like the beach.

55:28.850 --> 55:29.960
- Hey!

55:30.010 --> 55:32.280
Hey, baby, do you want
to stay here with daddy?

55:33.660 --> 55:34.440
- Yeah.

55:34.490 --> 55:35.270
You know what?

55:35.320 --> 55:36.520
You go have your fun.

55:36.570 --> 55:37.400
We'll stay.

55:38.270 --> 55:39.100
Ada!

55:48.040 --> 55:50.390
- I'm sweaty, dirty...

55:50.440 --> 55:51.440
- It's okay.

56:13.800 --> 56:14.870
- Marielle! You don't need

56:14.920 --> 56:16.080
to bring a bathing suit.

56:17.750 --> 56:19.930
Roland, I'm ready in five.

56:19.980 --> 56:21.450
Don't leave with me!

56:26.360 --> 56:27.190
- Fuck.

56:43.920 --> 56:44.940
- Where were you?

56:46.890 --> 56:49.060
- Getting to know
the house a little better.

56:54.650 --> 56:56.710
- I wanna go to the beach.

56:56.760 --> 56:58.270
I wanna go together.

56:59.450 --> 57:01.120
- Aren't you and daddy staying here?

57:01.170 --> 57:02.000
- It's okay.

57:02.950 --> 57:04.760
I can go with him.

57:04.810 --> 57:05.640
See you there?

57:15.510 --> 57:20.510
- I thought you'd look strange
in a dress, but you don't.

57:20.730 --> 57:21.560
- Okay.

57:25.730 --> 57:26.830
- It was a compliment.

57:27.970 --> 57:29.320
Let me try again.

57:33.060 --> 57:33.890
What's so funny?

57:35.450 --> 57:36.280
- Nothing.

57:39.090 --> 57:42.380
I just didn't think you'd be nervous too.

57:42.430 --> 57:43.520
- I'm not nervous.

57:46.060 --> 57:49.320
Hey, if the sun ruins your skin you're

57:49.370 --> 57:50.740
gonna lose your beauty

57:51.880 --> 57:55.170
and you'll only have your intellect left.

57:59.120 --> 58:00.540
Maybe I am a little nervous.

58:13.320 --> 58:16.530
- "If a plane lands in the
middle of the Sahara Desert

58:16.580 --> 58:20.080
and moves one grain
of sand one millimeter,

58:22.170 --> 58:23.130
what happens?"

58:23.180 --> 58:24.430
- I don't know.

58:27.930 --> 58:28.930
- Go for swim?

58:31.430 --> 58:32.830
- I'm one step ahead of you.

58:34.010 --> 58:36.060
Been waiting for a moment alone with you.

58:36.990 --> 58:39.010
Tomorrow night, picnic spot, you and me.

58:39.060 --> 58:41.060
- I don't like the two of them together.

58:42.640 --> 58:44.030
I know Adrienne and Hugo are

58:44.080 --> 58:45.590
having problems at the moment,

58:45.640 --> 58:47.160
but it's just not right.

58:48.550 --> 58:51.080
With Hugo right there
and Ada for God's sake.

59:04.630 --> 59:07.250
Marielle, how can you listen to this man?

59:07.300 --> 59:09.120
- It is called a sense of humor.

59:11.070 --> 59:12.580
We are here to relax, no?

59:19.250 --> 59:20.080
- Enough.

59:33.290 --> 59:36.040
- Oh, come here honey, come here.

59:37.080 --> 59:37.970
- Thank you.

59:42.260 --> 59:44.560
- That swim must have felt real nice.

59:46.140 --> 59:47.050
- What happened?

59:48.760 --> 59:49.540
- She fell over.

59:49.590 --> 59:50.420
Come on, now.

59:58.250 --> 59:59.630
Are you ok?

59:59.680 --> 1:00:00.520
Yeah.

1:00:03.700 --> 1:00:06.070
I'm happy to sleep on the couch tonight.

1:00:06.120 --> 1:00:08.200
I'll do whatever it takes.

1:00:08.250 --> 1:00:09.700
- What?

1:00:09.750 --> 1:00:11.720
- To make this work.

1:00:11.770 --> 1:00:13.020
Let's have another child.

1:00:14.290 --> 1:00:15.960
- Hugo, not now.

1:00:16.010 --> 1:00:17.520
I can't think right now.

1:00:17.570 --> 1:00:18.350
- You always

1:00:18.400 --> 1:00:19.610
overthink. Just say it.

1:00:19.660 --> 1:00:20.960
Just say how you feel.

1:00:21.830 --> 1:00:22.680
- I feel like

1:00:24.290 --> 1:00:27.360
I want you to be someone you're not.

1:00:30.410 --> 1:00:31.980
- You think you're better than me?

1:00:33.120 --> 1:00:34.120
You're not better.

1:00:34.170 --> 1:00:34.950
- I know.

1:00:35.000 --> 1:00:35.780
- You're worse.

1:00:35.830 --> 1:00:36.840
Come here.
- I know.

1:00:38.110 --> 1:00:38.900
- Let's go for a

1:00:38.950 --> 1:00:40.810
drive. Do you fancy a little nap?

1:00:46.280 --> 1:00:47.170
- Lucy!

1:00:47.220 --> 1:00:49.130
Let me back in, please!

1:00:55.780 --> 1:00:57.190
Oh, not now, kid.

1:01:01.620 --> 1:01:02.970
- Are you in love with her?

1:01:05.510 --> 1:01:06.350
- Who?

1:01:11.960 --> 1:01:12.800
Marielle.

1:01:20.380 --> 1:01:22.670
- What the hell is going on here?

1:01:22.720 --> 1:01:24.210
Get out of my property.

1:01:25.560 --> 1:01:27.690
You're a disgraceful

1:01:27.740 --> 1:01:29.100
"Son of a bitch"

1:01:29.150 --> 1:01:29.990
as you say.

1:01:31.370 --> 1:01:33.000
You worthless, dirty scum.

1:01:33.050 --> 1:01:34.750
You should be ashamed of yourself.

1:01:42.290 --> 1:01:45.580
I think they'll be fine.

1:01:45.630 --> 1:01:46.880
- I'm not so sure.

1:01:48.530 --> 1:01:49.520
- Teaser.

1:01:56.000 --> 1:01:59.000
- Well, I don't suppose there's
anything we can do about it.

1:02:03.410 --> 1:02:05.330
What happened, darling?

1:02:06.880 --> 1:02:08.270
What happened to your dress?

1:02:08.320 --> 1:02:09.290
- Nothing.

1:02:09.340 --> 1:02:12.210
I went for a little hike
back there and it ripped.

1:02:13.700 --> 1:02:14.550
- Be careful, hm?

1:02:23.250 --> 1:02:24.510
- Can I have some?

1:02:24.560 --> 1:02:25.400
- What?

1:02:31.530 --> 1:02:32.360
Why not?

1:02:55.530 --> 1:02:56.370
- Hugo.

1:02:57.900 --> 1:02:59.250
Hugo.

1:02:59.300 --> 1:03:00.130
- Oh fuck.

1:03:04.990 --> 1:03:07.330
What the hell are you doing?

1:03:10.050 --> 1:03:12.450
Is this your version of
trying to become closer?

1:03:13.970 --> 1:03:15.020
- It was an accident.

1:03:30.890 --> 1:03:31.810
Adrienne!

1:03:40.240 --> 1:03:42.610
He never actually did any work.

1:03:46.700 --> 1:03:48.120
- Give me a drag.

1:03:50.770 --> 1:03:51.670
- You don't smoke.

1:03:58.970 --> 1:04:02.310
- I've never brought anyone here before.

1:04:08.720 --> 1:04:11.220
I told you it was a good spot.

1:04:12.730 --> 1:04:14.440
You're so special, Marielle.

1:04:26.100 --> 1:04:27.640
- Let's stay here forever.

1:04:38.240 --> 1:04:40.220
- Now you'll always remember me.

1:05:07.470 --> 1:05:08.250
- You know what? I

1:05:08.300 --> 1:05:09.080
don't know where

1:05:09.130 --> 1:05:10.290
Nick is. He should be

1:05:11.930 --> 1:05:13.630
here already. Clear up this mess.

1:05:16.760 --> 1:05:18.270
- I'm sure we'll sort it out.

1:05:20.090 --> 1:05:20.920
- Really?

1:05:22.600 --> 1:05:23.860
You're still trusting him?

1:05:25.830 --> 1:05:26.610
- I'll be back.

1:05:26.660 --> 1:05:28.070
I can't look at this chaos.

1:05:29.000 --> 1:05:30.600
- I'm sorry I let him touch you.

1:05:32.050 --> 1:05:33.910
Mummy, can I come with you?

1:05:47.430 --> 1:05:48.580
Why are we stopping?

1:05:48.630 --> 1:05:49.960
- Shh, be quiet.

1:06:23.080 --> 1:06:25.190
- We're all very upset.

1:06:26.380 --> 1:06:27.210
- "Blanche".

1:06:31.230 --> 1:06:32.060
What happened?

1:06:48.210 --> 1:06:51.940
- The house is nothing like this.

1:06:54.080 --> 1:06:55.160
It feels rotten.

1:06:56.480 --> 1:06:57.420
It's broken.

1:06:58.430 --> 1:07:01.850
It's stinks of distrust and secrets

1:07:01.900 --> 1:07:03.570
and dirty little corners.

1:07:06.750 --> 1:07:09.080
The good at this house is crumpled.

1:07:10.160 --> 1:07:15.160
It's turned to dust, turned to
ashes along with Nana Lottie,

1:07:15.810 --> 1:07:20.230
and you have taken away
its purity, its innocence,

1:07:20.280 --> 1:07:22.630
and her beautiful, naive spirit.

1:07:24.510 --> 1:07:26.020
She wasn't at Claire's, mum.

1:07:32.880 --> 1:07:33.660
- I have an update

1:07:33.710 --> 1:07:34.670
regarding her role.

1:07:34.720 --> 1:07:37.640
- Yeah, I'm afraid she's
in a meeting right now.

1:07:37.690 --> 1:07:39.200
I can give her the bad news.

1:07:40.500 --> 1:07:42.600
- I don't know what all the fuss is about.

1:07:42.650 --> 1:07:44.250
I could have it fixed like that.

1:07:46.820 --> 1:07:47.650
- You tell him.

1:07:48.630 --> 1:07:52.990
- Now listen here, we are very unsatisfied

1:07:53.040 --> 1:07:54.760
with your so-called results.

1:07:56.030 --> 1:07:59.290
You better leave her and all
of us alone before I sue you.

1:08:01.110 --> 1:08:04.510
- And before I kick this in
your sad, pathetic little balls!

1:08:05.560 --> 1:08:06.400
- The fuck?

1:08:07.650 --> 1:08:09.490
- Nana, you got the part!

1:08:09.540 --> 1:08:11.580
Congratulations, mum.

1:08:11.630 --> 1:08:13.800
- My little superstar!

1:08:16.790 --> 1:08:17.620
Well done.

1:08:19.310 --> 1:08:20.700
- Congratulations.

1:08:23.640 --> 1:08:27.420
Our very own Blanche Deboise.

1:08:27.470 --> 1:08:28.440
- It's DuBois.

1:08:30.380 --> 1:08:31.880
What are you still doing here?

1:08:41.200 --> 1:08:43.700
- You're all fucking amateurs!

1:09:18.540 --> 1:09:19.540
- I'm sorry.

1:09:22.190 --> 1:09:23.020
I'm sorry.

1:09:25.240 --> 1:09:28.650
It's all ruined.

1:09:43.560 --> 1:09:45.160
- So this is where she puts you.

1:09:46.150 --> 1:09:47.650
- What?

1:09:47.700 --> 1:09:48.680
- I'm curious...

1:09:51.040 --> 1:09:54.060
Do you get off on the image of
your woman with another man?

1:09:54.110 --> 1:09:55.010
- Repeat that?

1:09:55.850 --> 1:09:56.630
- Why haven't you

1:09:56.680 --> 1:09:57.520
hit me already?

1:09:58.620 --> 1:10:00.600
- I'm not usually a violent man.

1:10:01.490 --> 1:10:02.320
- That's cute.

1:10:03.290 --> 1:10:05.130
I bet she loves that about you.

1:10:11.320 --> 1:10:15.760
You know, I'm not the
one that came onto her.

1:10:18.510 --> 1:10:19.340
- Daddy.

1:10:20.400 --> 1:10:21.500
- You're not worth it.

1:10:25.890 --> 1:10:26.890
- Excuse me, ladies.

1:10:57.120 --> 1:10:59.180
We're both
guilty of this, Nadine.

1:10:59.230 --> 1:11:02.030
That bastard took her there on our dime.

1:11:09.950 --> 1:11:11.000
- Come here, sweetie.

1:11:13.370 --> 1:11:14.210
Come here.

1:11:20.860 --> 1:11:25.460
I had no idea just how lost you were.

1:11:25.510 --> 1:11:27.230
You should have come to me.

1:11:28.740 --> 1:11:30.120
I am your mother.

1:11:31.290 --> 1:11:32.640
I'll always be here.

1:11:39.770 --> 1:11:41.320
- Do you think you can hurt me?

1:11:42.530 --> 1:11:45.080
Do you think you're daddy's little hero?

1:11:45.130 --> 1:11:46.130
- I'm a tough girl.

1:11:47.650 --> 1:11:50.070
Don't touch her, or my mother!

1:12:56.890 --> 1:13:00.300
I didn't
want to wake her. Is that okay?

1:13:00.350 --> 1:13:01.350
- Of course.

1:13:07.400 --> 1:13:08.650
Can I sit down?

1:13:11.440 --> 1:13:13.140
- Nana Lottie's cure for sunburns.

1:13:17.520 --> 1:13:18.460
- Here.

1:13:18.510 --> 1:13:20.520
Let me do it for you.

1:13:20.570 --> 1:13:21.490
I'll help.

1:13:39.730 --> 1:13:43.140
Mum? I think...

1:13:44.500 --> 1:13:48.780
- It would be a good idea
to go to the dermatologist.

1:13:49.940 --> 1:13:50.770
- Thank you.

1:13:51.790 --> 1:13:53.960
What happened to you knee?

1:13:56.850 --> 1:14:00.810
- The gynecologist, sorry.

1:14:00.860 --> 1:14:01.690
- What?

1:14:03.290 --> 1:14:06.950
Marielle, are you pregnant?

1:14:07.000 --> 1:14:09.230
Mum no!

1:14:09.280 --> 1:14:13.430
- It's just, I mean, you know,

1:14:13.480 --> 1:14:16.070
since I'm starting university this year.

1:14:19.340 --> 1:14:20.360
- Are you mad at me?

1:14:26.390 --> 1:14:27.170
- This is why

1:14:27.220 --> 1:14:29.100
we don't trust guys like that, Nadine.

1:14:30.870 --> 1:14:34.200
He's been with our 18 year
old daughter, for God's sakes.

1:14:34.250 --> 1:14:35.470
- I'm glad you can count.

1:14:35.520 --> 1:14:38.170
- Oh, do you think this is a joke?

1:14:38.220 --> 1:14:39.300
- I'll fix it.

1:14:39.350 --> 1:14:40.130
- How?

1:14:40.180 --> 1:14:42.630
- Well, I spend time with her

1:14:42.680 --> 1:14:45.900
and work hard for the family
with the bed and breakfast.

1:14:45.950 --> 1:14:47.070
- Bullshit.

1:14:47.120 --> 1:14:48.240
- Excuse me?

1:14:48.290 --> 1:14:49.680
- Well, now that you're gonna

1:14:49.730 --> 1:14:52.270
in the theater, you're gonna
forget about this BnB idea.

1:14:52.320 --> 1:14:53.910
It will never work.

1:14:59.160 --> 1:15:00.950
- What was that for?

1:15:01.000 --> 1:15:02.980
This is not the right timing.

1:15:04.260 --> 1:15:05.120
- I don't know.

1:15:06.120 --> 1:15:09.370
I think there was a hidden
compliment in there somewhere.

1:15:12.980 --> 1:15:13.810
Let's go, love.

1:15:17.170 --> 1:15:20.750
- Ada, you know I love you so much.

1:15:24.240 --> 1:15:29.240
You and daddy are gonna have a blast the
rest of the summer and then you're gonna

1:15:29.960 --> 1:15:31.710
be a big girl for me like

1:15:31.760 --> 1:15:32.810
we talked about.

1:15:38.160 --> 1:15:39.190
I'll miss you.

1:15:40.750 --> 1:15:41.650
I have to do this.

1:15:50.200 --> 1:15:51.150
- I'm proud of you.

1:15:54.300 --> 1:15:55.850
Ada, see you, bud.

1:15:56.870 --> 1:15:57.650
Come on.

1:15:57.700 --> 1:15:58.780
- Where are you going?

1:16:00.640 --> 1:16:01.660
- For a ride around.

1:16:02.860 --> 1:16:03.760
- Marielle, don't.

1:16:04.940 --> 1:16:06.490
- Adrienne, trust me.

1:16:07.710 --> 1:16:09.260
I have to do this.

1:16:47.160 --> 1:16:49.300
Is this where you live?

1:16:49.350 --> 1:16:52.020
This isn't a good idea.

1:16:53.610 --> 1:16:55.220
- Are you...

1:16:55.270 --> 1:16:56.060
homeless?

1:16:56.110 --> 1:16:57.610
- Get out of here!

1:16:59.640 --> 1:17:01.400
- You have our blanket.

1:17:25.640 --> 1:17:27.750
The stillness is misleading.

1:17:27.800 --> 1:17:30.380
Those intimate, beautiful mornings were

1:17:32.440 --> 1:17:35.570
misleading. I needed to know for sure
that it meant nothing.

1:17:40.730 --> 1:17:41.910
I hurt the people who

1:17:41.960 --> 1:17:43.450
love me so I wanted to get hurt.

1:17:44.950 --> 1:17:46.710
Even after everything they have

1:17:46.760 --> 1:17:47.690
forgiven me.

1:17:49.810 --> 1:17:51.920
Just like that. I need to do right by them.

1:19:09.410 --> 1:19:10.490
I'm home now.

1:19:20.910 --> 1:19:22.600
- Where'd you learn to do that?

1:19:23.670 --> 1:19:27.490
- Just a couple of easy tricks
I learned from a stranger.

1:19:48.870 --> 1:19:52.290
“...Returning home as a French belle
Back in England, I sing farewell”

1:21:28.020 --> 1:21:30.080
- You sure you don't
want me to come with you?

1:21:30.130 --> 1:21:31.130
- No, maman.

1:21:31.180 --> 1:21:32.650
You have the BnB now.

1:21:32.700 --> 1:21:33.800
You have to stay here.

1:21:34.890 --> 1:21:36.480
I'm going to be really happy.

1:21:36.530 --> 1:21:37.930
- I want to know everything.

1:21:38.980 --> 1:21:40.160
All the photos you take,

1:21:40.210 --> 1:21:42.310
even the bad ones, you send to me, okay?

1:21:42.360 --> 1:21:43.490
- I will, maman.
